{"action": "input", "code": "def main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    point_color = find_point_color(input_grid)\n    template = find_non_point_color_pixels(input_grid, point_color)\n    object = find_same_color_pixels(input_grid, point_color)\n    input_grid = copy_surrounding_pixels(input_grid, template, object)\n    input_grid = lengthen_line_around_object(input_grid, object)\n    return input_grid\ndef find_point_color(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> int:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid, this function finds the color of a pixel and its neighbors\n    if they are of the same color.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n\n    Returns:\n    An integer representing the color of the pixel and its neighbors if they are of the same color.\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = input_grid.shape\n    for i in range(rows):\n        for j in range(cols):\n            color = input_grid[i][j]\n            if i > 0 and input_grid[i - 1][j] == color:\n                return color\n            elif j > 0 and input_grid[i][j - 1] == color:\n                return color\n            elif i < rows - 1 and input_grid[i + 1][j] == color:\n                return color\n            elif j < cols - 1 and input_grid[i][j + 1] == color:\n                return color\n    return -1\ndef find_non_point_color_pixels(input_grid: np.ndarray, point_color: int) -> np.ndarray:\n    \"\"\"\n    Given an input grid and a point color, this function finds the pixels of point_color and their neighbors\n    that are not of the same color.\n\n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the input grid.\n    point_color: An integer representing the color of the pixel and its neighbors if they are of the same color.\n\n    Returns:\n    A numpy array representing the pixels of point_color and their neighbors that are not of the same color.\n    \"\"\"\n    rows, cols = input_grid.shape\n    non_point_color_pixels = np.zeros((rows, cols))\n    for i in rang